mechanoreception.notes: Sea cucumbers possess mechanoreceptors for detecting touch and water currents, essential for locomotion and feeding. Inferred based on general knowledge of sea cucumbers.

chemoreception.notes: Sea cucumbers use chemoreceptors to detect chemical cues in the water, aiding in food localization and mate recognition. Inferred based on general knowledge of sea cucumbers.

photoreception.notes: The presence or absence of photoreceptors in Pseudostichopodidae is currently unknown.
